          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "the target used were natural argon gas of 1 bar",
                "pressure in stainless steel cells with 10 micron",
                "Ti windows."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "STTA",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " single and stacked cells were",
                "irradiated with extracted alpha beam at 500 Na beam",
                "current. The bombarding charge was integrated by a",
                "Faraday-cup and was also monitored via monitor",
                "reactions on copper. The single cell irradiations",
                "were carried out at the debrecen mgc20 cyclotron,",
                "and the stacked cells were irradiated at the Julich",
                "CV28 compact cyclotron using 20.4 And 26.7 MeV primary",
                "beam energy respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "AREA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " normal high resolution gamma-spectrometry",
                "was applied. Nuclear data were taken from E. Browne",
                "and R.B.Firestone, Table of Radioactive Isotopes,",
                "edited by V.S shirley, Wiley, New York, 1986.",
                "the energy degradation was calculated using the",
                "tables of williamson et al.,Report, CEA-R-3042 and",
                "J.F. Ziegler Handbook of stopping cross sections for",
                "energetic ions in all elements, vol.5, Pergamon,Oxford,",
                "1980."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "EN-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the error of the energy includes the",
                "primary dispersion of the incident beam, the",
                "uncertainty by the straggling effect and the density",
                "reduction in the gas cells along the beam strike.",
                "the typical uncertainty of the energy is about 1. MeV",
                "near the threshold and 0.3 MeV around 20 MeV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the overall error in the cross section",
                "determination includes the errors:",
                "    flux measurements             8%",
                "    statistical error           1-5%",
                "    detector efficiency error     5%",
                "    nuclear data uncertaintty     3%",
                "    effective target thickness    5%",
                "total estimated error in the cross section values  was",
                "about 12%."
              ]
            }
          ],
